FBIS3-60844 "jptot001__l94092" JPRS-TOT-94-001-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 7 January 1994 CENTRAL EURASIA RUSSIA Four Caucasians Kidnap Children; No Motive Given Kidnappers Say They Have AIDS Moscow Radio Rossii Network in Russian 1700GMT 23 Dec 93 Moscow Radio Rossii Network Language: Russian Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] [passage omitted] According to a Foreign Minister spokesman, an emergency group has contacted Iran's Embassy in Moscow and Russia's ambassador to Tehran. The ambassador was instructed to inform the leadership of Iran of the events which have taken place so that they can also monitor the situation. [passage omitted] [Moscow ITAR-TASS in English at 1727 GMT on 23 December, in a Rostov-datelined report on the hijacking, adds the following: "A helicopter carrying four terrorists and hostages took off from a military airfield in Rostov-on-Don, southern Russian at 19:20 Moscow time on Thursday. [passage omitted] "The four armed and masked terrorists armed with automatic guns and carrying boxes of explosives were earlier reported to have announced they were all infected with AIDS and had nothing to lose. Nonetheless, they asked for warm clothes and food for the children and their woman teacher they had taken hostage."]
